msIdentifier.collection: John Frederick Lewis Collection of European Manuscripts

msContents.summary: This manuscript is a sixteenth-century Missal, following the use of Rome, from the Southern Netherlands. It is highly decorated, including twenty-two historiated initials.

msItem.title: Temporale, containing Masses for Christmas, Saint Stephen, Epiphany, Last Supper, Easter, Ascension, Pentecost, and the Feast of Corpus Christi
Ordo Missae, noted (begins imperfectly), followed by Prefaces
Mass for Blessing of Candles, incomplete (decoration incomplete)

supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil, upper right

p.signatures: Signatures throughout; print-style signatures, with the first four leaves of a quire identified by a number plus a letter (e.g., D1, D2, D3, D4), and the last four leaves unmarked

p.catchwords: Catchwords throughout, lower right verso, written vertically; catchwords are also occasionally written on leaves that are not the final leaf of the quire, and on the recto

layoutDesc.layout: Written area: 224 x 145 mm; 1 column of 15 lines; Occasionally with five four-line staves; rubricated headings describing the introit appear before each historiated initial, blue ink ruling, prickings visible

decoDesc.decoNote: Twenty-two Historiated initials, five borders of flora and fauna, two smaller historiated initials, approximately three hundred illuminated and decorated letters.
14vHistoriated initial C, Stoning of Saint Stephen
28vHistoriated initial N, True Cross with monograms ihs and ma on altar
111rHistoriated initial U, Virgin and Child in radiance
136rHistoriated initial T, Mass of Saint Gregory
149rHistoriated initial G, Virgin praying surrounded by her symbols
155rHistoriated initial S, Presentation of Christ at the Temple
172vHistoriated initial D, Saint John the Baptist with book
179vHistoriated initial N, Saints Peter and Paul
193rHistoriated initial S, Saint Martin and beggar
198vHistoriated initial G, Assumption of the Virgin
205vHistoriated initial G, Nativity of the Virgin
213vHistoriated initial G, Dedication of a church
228vHistoriated initial R, Allegory of Death with three skulls and bone
242rHistoriated initial S, Saint Martin and the beggar

binding.p: French, blind-stamped dark green morocco by Belz-Niedrée with superexlibris of the Bibliothèque de Mello on both covers, parchment doublures in gold-tooled frame, early twentieth century

history.provenance: Baron François Florentin Achille Seillière, Paris (1813-1873); sale, Sotheby's, London, February 28, 1887; catalogue description of Tregaskis (London bookseller) pasted onto back flyleaf; John Frederick Lewis, Philadelphia; given by his widow, Anne Baker Lewis, to the Free Library of Philadelphia in 1936; inscribed on the front inner flyleaf: "From the collection of Baron Seillière Missale Romanum ms. on vellum, XV century. 263 leaves, 300 large initials in gold and colors. 23 miniatures, 5 pages with borders. 'Bibliothèque de Mello' armorial binding by Belz- Niedrée."
